    "subtitle": "A five-axis personality snapshot for venture builders, using public-domain IPIP items.",
    "description": "<p>There is no single type of founder. Personality only explains part of how someone builds — but it shapes what drains you, what you avoid, and where you need a complement. This snapshot maps five traits relevant to venture work, not as scores to maximize, but as positions on axes that each have a cost and a use.</p><p>Answer about how you actually are, not how you wish to be. Both poles of every axis have value depending on context.</p>",
    "duration": "20 items. Approximately three minutes.",
    "privacyNote": "Your answers stay in this browser. The result belongs to you. Sharing is your choice.",
    "disclaimer": "This is a short reflective snapshot, not a clinical or validated psychometric assessment. It uses public-domain IPIP items but is not the full IPIP scale.",
    "startButton": "Map my traits"
  },
